  "description": "<p>Go fast and light in the bitter cold. The Andes Infinium 800 sleeping bag will keep you warm down to -23, but it won't weigh you down thanks to a slim cut and premium 800-fill-power down insulation. The water-resistant GORE-TEX INFINIUM\u2122 shell fabric and Nikwax Hydrophobic down add protection from drippy snow caves or condensation-soaked tent walls.</p><ul><li>Outer fabric is water-resistant yet breathable GORE-TEX INFINIUM\u2122 with WINDSTOPPER\u00ae technology</li><li>Hood and footbox are lined with water-resistant GORE-TEX INFINIUM\u2122 fabric to stand up to condensation</li><li>Insulated with premium 800-fill-power down that provides exceptional warmth for its weight</li><li>Nikwax Hydrophobic treatment ensures the down absorbs less water, dries faster and retains loft better than conventional down</li><li>Down is ethically sourced from European geese and meets the Responsible Down Standard for animal welfare</li><li>A close-fitting neck baffle, face baffle and adjustable hood keep the cold from sneaking in</li><li>Longitudinal baffles in the chest and foot minimize down migration</li><li>3/4-length zipper saves weight without restricting entry and exit</li><li>Internal zippered pocket protects your contact lenses or headlamp from the cold</li><li>Includes a cotton home storage sack and a dry bag\u2013style compression sack</li></ul>",
